<br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Our members are not an active part of the &quot;community as a whole.&quot; We prefer to keep to ourselves and play the game we love so much as a close-knit guild.<br>
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
That to me is a polite way of saying &quot;We rule, you suck, We are bigger, and you still suck.&quot;<br>
<br>
You don't wanna be a part of the community fine, you all wanna be jerks. FINE! But the minute you start stepping on other players cause they are X amount of minutes to getting a raid force together, and you just got yours finished, then start throwing the PnP FCFS rules in Peeps faces well then your just a bunch of cowardly Jerks. <br>
<br>
I say Blayze is right, at least he intends to use his epic for the COMMUNITY, and he IS an active member of the community. So he supposidly needs to back step a few and get a couple more drops. So what. From day one we all knew the end game Raids would be mainly Unroleplayed, Even Skathris will group with there Enemies on a raid situation. Hell if I was at Raid level and Shintou asked me to help him with his epic I'd say yes, Then after he got it I would go IC and whoop him good. Point is don't try and throw RP in our faces and expect us to take it. <br>
<br>
And as far as Awakened Souls go, all you need to do is add another &quot;S&quot; word on your guild tag so we can appropriatly refer to you as &quot;ASS&quot; which the majority of you are.<br>
<br>
PS: If I hurt ASS's feelings good. If your offended, then thats even better. I now know that AS will never get any help from me when I reach the appropriate level, and thats too bad cause In my opinion I am the best at playing the class I am, and that class is Ranger. Sure you may bash Rangers but that only means you don't understand us. Good day.<br>
